The President of the Mike Omotosho Foundation, Dr. Mike Omotosho, has said that corporate social responsibility should be a vital part of the corporate business culture, especially for startups. Omotosho said while it might be easier for startups to integrate CSR in their DNA, older, more established businesses might struggle to see the benefit of doing good. He, however, gave reasons why both established businesses and startups should take CSR more seriously.  Watch the video